          "type": "text",
          "text": "Perfect! ✅ Your 7-segment counter is ready. Here's what I built:\n\n**Hardware:**\n- 7-segment display (cathode common) with 7 current-limiting resistors (220Ω each) on pins 2–8\n- Button on pin 9 with INPUT_PULLUP (pulls to GND when pressed)\n- GND rail distribution for the display and button\n\n**Sketch:**\n- Counter starts at 0 and increments 0–9 on each button press, then wraps back to 0\n- Uses a `displayDigit()` function that maps each number (0–9) to the correct segment pattern\n- Debounces the button by tracking `lastBtnState` — only counts a press when the button transitions from HIGH to LOW\n\nPress the button to increment the counter on the display!"
        }
      ]
